{"questionId":"9075070","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Yellow light from a sodium lamp of wavelength 590 nm is incident at normal incidence&nbsp;on a double slit. The resulting interference pattern is observed on a screen.&nbsp;The intensity of the pattern on the screen is shown.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/781241175cdb39d6ce12aca4b7cb635d901cc008.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The distance from the centre of the pattern to A is 4.1&nbsp;x 10<sup>–2</sup> m. The distance from&nbsp;the screen to the slits is 7.0 m.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/bfa0533d09b42aa681d8c983e6378a744306785d.png\"></p>\n<p>Calculate the width of each slit.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>θ</em> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{4.1 \\times {{10}^{ - 2}}}}{{7.0}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4.1</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7.0</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<em><strong>OR</strong> b</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{\\lambda }{\\theta }\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>λ</mi>\n    <mi>θ</mi>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> «= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{7.0 \\times 5.9 \\times {{10}^{ - 7}}}}{{4.1 \\times {{10}^{ - 2}}}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7.0</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>5.9</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>7</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4.1</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mn>10</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>−</mo>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mrow>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>»</p>\n<p>1.0 × 10<sup>–4</sup> «m»</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[0]</strong> for use of double slit formula (which gives the correct answer so do not award BCA) </em></p>\n<p><em>Allow use of sin or tan for small angles</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9075070","referenceCode":"17N.2.HL.TZ0.6a.ii","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The distance from the centre of the pattern to A is 4.1 x 10–2 m. The distance from the screen to the slits is 7.0 m. Calculate the width of each slit.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.3 – Interference","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}